ynasty, in 1764 and moved south to New Bern. Widowed by the Revolution, she married again and lived to seventy-nine in Craven County — a long way from her father’s pulpit."}],"slug":"eunice-edwards-1743"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}